Final PhD Thesis — Héctor Carrión (UCSC), July 2026 defense

Build:
    make          # runs pdflatex -> bibtex -> pdflatex -> pdflatex
    make clean

Overleaf:
    zip -r Final_Thesis.zip Final_Thesis
    upload Final_Thesis.zip as a new Overleaf project
    set the main document to final_thesis.tex

Structure:
    final_thesis.tex     main document
    final_thesis.bib     merged bibliography
    ucthesis.cls         UCSC thesis class (unmodified)
    uct{10,11,12}.clo    UCSC thesis font-size options (unmodified)
    HealNet/             Chapter 2 figures
    FEDD/                Chapter 3 figures
    cgDDI/               Chapter 4 figures
    DermDepth/           Chapter 5 figures

Chapters:
    1. Introduction
    2. Representation Learning, Heal-Stages (HealNet)
    3. Representation Learning, Fairness and Efficiency (FEDD)
    4. Controllable Generation, Fairness and Data Efficiency (cgDDI)
    5. Monocular Metric 3D Reconstruction for Dermatology (DermDepth)
    6. Conclusion and Future Work
